snippet.title: My Trans Girlfriend Doesn't Make Me Gay | LOVE DON'T JUDGE
snippet.description:
SUBSCRIBE to Truly: http://bit.ly/Oc61Hj

A TRANSGENDER woman has reconnected with her ‘handsome jock’ high school crush after finishing her transitioning journey. Victoria, 22, has been in a relationship with Chris, 23, for a year and a half after swiping right on Tinder. However, they had met years before, having attended the same high school in Rhode Island, where Victoria was relentlessly bullied. At the time she was transitioning from male to female, something that many of the town’s conservative community would ridicule her for. Victoria told Truly: “I’d have kids spitting on me, throwing trash, telling me to go kill myself.” Some of Chris’ friends would even be a part of bullying Victoria, a painful memory for him now.

Follow their story here:
https://www.instagram.com/thevivirose/
https://youtube.com/channel/vfawnbeauty

Videographer: Marcus Cooper
Producer: Kate Moore, Ruby Coote
Editor: Garry Sykes
